# C++ UI test verification (agents)

UI tests under `src/__test__/ui/` open an SDL window for **manual** inspection. They run until the user closes them (Q or window close) and may last minutes. They are not automated unit tests.

Test runners under `test-runners/` require **Node.js** (see `DEVELOPMENT.md`).

## Agent rule

When verifying UI tests (or UI-related changes), **compile only — do not run the test executable**.

- Do **not** run `scripts/run-ui-tests-ucrt64.sh` in automation.
- Do **not** run UI tests via `test-runners/ui/*.sh` without `--build-only`.
- Do **not** run the UI section of `scripts/run-acceptance-ucrt64.sh` in automation.

Running UI tests leaves windows open and blocks until a human closes each one.

## How to verify

**One test** (`--build-only` passes through the shell wrapper):

```powershell
.\scripts\Invoke-Ucrt64.ps1 "test-runners/ui/TestConfirmModal.sh --build-only"
```

```bash
test-runners/ui/TestConfirmModal.sh --build-only
```

**All UI tests** (compile every UI test, no execution):

```powershell
.\scripts\Invoke-Ucrt64.ps1 "./scripts/compile-ui-tests.sh"
```

```bash
./scripts/compile-ui-tests.sh
```

A successful compile (exit code 0) is sufficient verification. Leave interactive visual checks to the user.

## Other C++ tests

Runner, DB loader, and model tests under `src/__test__/runner/`, `src/__test__/db/`, and `src/__test__/model/` **do** finish on their own — agents may run those normally via `test-runners/`.
